description: Description is the fiction-writing mode for transmitting a mental image of the particulars of a story. Together with dialogue, narration, exposition, and summarization, description is one of the most widely recognized of the fiction-writing modes. The most appropriate and effective techniques for presenting description are a matter of ongoing discussion among writers and writing coaches.
